		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Business architecture</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:422px;"><a href="/wiki/File:NIH_IT_Enterprise_Architecture_Framework.jpg" class="image" title="Example of the NIH IT Enterprise Architecture Framework, where the Business architecture is pictured as part of the enterprise architecture."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/NIH_IT_Enterprise_Architecture_Framework.jpg/420px-NIH_IT_Enterprise_Architecture_Framework.jpg" width="420" height="330" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:NIH_IT_Enterprise_Architecture_Framework.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Example of the <a href="/wiki/NIH" title="NIH" class="mw-redirect">NIH</a> IT Enterprise Architecture Framework, where the Business architecture is pictured as part of the <a href="/wiki/Enterprise_architecture" title="Enterprise architecture">enterprise architecture</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>A <b>business architecture</b> is an organizing <a href="/wiki/Enterprise_architecture_framework" title="Enterprise architecture framework" class="mw-redirect">framework</a> of a <a href="/wiki/Business" title="Business">business</a>, and the <a href="/wiki/Document" title="Document">documents</a> and <a href="/wiki/Diagram" title="Diagram">diagrams</a> that describe that structure or the people who help build such a structure, respectively.</p>
<p>Business architecture is close related to concepts <a href="/wiki/Enterprise_architecture" title="Enterprise architecture">enterprise architecture</a> and <a href="/wiki/Business_reference_model" title="Business reference model">business reference model</a>.</p>
